const summaries = { lastRace: "Nora topped the JPN leaderboard with 47 points — more than double the 22.27 league average — powered by Oscar Piastri's 43-point turnaround after two straight DNFs. Mary Beth (2 pts) and David (3 pts) were the weekend's biggest losers, with Lance Stroll's third consecutive DNF burying Mary Beth yet again. Kimi Antonelli added another 50 points for Timo, though Oliver Bearman's DNF left real points on the table.", season: "Timo leads the league at 190 points, 37 clear of Margaret in second, with Kimi Antonelli's 150-point season tally the best individual driver haul in the entire field. Margaret is the most dangerous challenger — George Russell (111 pts) has been consistently brilliant and the lineup hasn't posted a negative race score all year. Charlie props up the table at just 6 points total; Alonso's two DNFs and -17-point season make him one of the most damaging roster picks in the league.", players: { "Alyssa": "4th overall at 105 points, but Max Verstappen's race contributions have slid from 50 to 14 to 13 and your combined race totals have declined every single round (54, 34, 17). Perez chips in a modest 28 pts — the lineup is functional but firmly trending in the wrong direction.", "Nora": "6th at 50 points, though JPN's 47-point round tells a much better story — Piastri finally delivered a 43-point race after two DNFs torched your early season, and Colapinto has been quietly steady at 28 pts. If Piastri stays on track, Nora is a genuine climber.", "Jay": "10th with just 24 points, and Bottas is the problem — sitting at -11 for the season after multiple DNFs, he's eaten through most of what Norris (35 pts) has produced. A lineup with one solid driver and one liability is a brutal spot to be in.", "Margaret": "2nd overall at 153 points and the most reliable lineup in the league — Russell (111 pts) and Ocon (42 pts) have both been positive in every single race this season. If Timo has an off week, Margaret is the obvious beneficiary.", "Cecelia": "3rd at 113 points with the most consistent race-to-race output in the league (42, 37, 34), built almost entirely on Leclerc's 111-point season. Bortoleto has contributed just 2 pts total after a brutal -14 in CHN, but Leclerc's floor is high enough it hasn't cost Cecelia yet.", "Timo": "League leader at 190 points and it isn't close — Antonelli's 150-point season is the best individual driver tally in the field, and that CHN 102-point haul was genuinely ridiculous. Bearman's JPN DNF was the only real blemish; no one else has this ceiling.", "Mary Beth": "9th at 38 points, dragged down by Lance Stroll's catastrophic season — a DNF in every single race has left him at -54, the worst driver total in the league by a country mile. Hamilton (92 pts) is doing everything right; the lineup simply cannot survive Stroll's ongoing damage.", "Jane": "5th at 66 points with Lawson (50 pts) doing the real work, including a 35-point CHN performance. Hadjar (16 pts) has been inconsistent after an AUS DNF, but if both drivers fire together Jane has genuine upside from here.", "David": "8th at 41 points — Sainz has held up his end at 41 pts but Albon's CHN DNF left him with a zero on the season, and a combined 3 points in JPN is the kind of result that cements a bottom-half finish. David needs both cars crossing the line to climb.", "Charlie": "Dead last at 6 points, and Alonso is the primary reason — two DNFs and -17 pts on the season make him one of the most damaging picks in the league. Lindblad has done what he can at 23 pts, but no one can carry a roster through that kind of damage alone.", "Sarah": "7th at 42 points, with Gasly (45 pts) providing a steady foundation after Hulkenberg's AUS DNF sent the opening round to -9. Back-to-back positive races since then are encouraging, but with a mid-tier duo, the ceiling here is probably close to where Sarah's already sitting." } };
